From: Florian Maurer <fmaurer@disroot.org>
Date: Sun, 19 Apr 2026 16:29:40 +0000
Subject: ipq806x: uboot-envtools: match appsblenv label case-insensitively

The Aruba AP-325 DTS labels its U-Boot env partition "0:appsblenv"
(lowercase) via qcom,smem-part, so the grep in ubootenv_mtdinfo never
matches and /etc/config/ubootenv stays empty.  Making the grep
case-insensitive keeps the existing uppercase-APPSBLENV consumers
(qcom,ipq8064-ap148, qcom,ipq8064-db149) working and lets the AP-325
stanza auto-configure fw_printenv/fw_setenv.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>

diff --git a/package/boot/uboot-envtools/files/ipq806x b/package/boot/uboot-envtools/files/ipq806x
index 443a0e13d40deb95ba1e5ca44c1cce632baed574..c0d11b70d7d6c15348b87742b89e5c2a7d4061bb 100644
--- a/package/boot/uboot-envtools/files/ipq806x
+++ b/package/boot/uboot-envtools/files/ipq806x
@@ -12,7 +12,7 @@ touch /etc/config/ubootenv
 board=$(board_name)
 
 ubootenv_mtdinfo () {
-	UBOOTENV_PART=$(cat /proc/mtd | grep APPSBLENV)
+	UBOOTENV_PART=$(cat /proc/mtd | grep -i APPSBLENV)
 	mtd_dev=$(echo $UBOOTENV_PART | awk '{print $1}' | sed 's/:$//')
 	mtd_size=$(echo $UBOOTENV_PART | awk '{print "0x"$2}')
 	mtd_erase=$(echo $UBOOTENV_PART | awk '{print "0x"$3}')
